comments.body:
@josh11b @mrry Sorry for late. How about these words as the comment for `
share_session_state_in_clusterspec_propagation`.
```text
// In default, everything works as before when cluster propagation is enabled.
// However, when `share_session_state_in_clusterspec_propagation` is turned on,
// the `isolate_session_state` field will be forced to be true even if you set
// it to false in code. Then, all resources will be shared among worker sessions
// in the same TF Server, just like the case where clusterspec propagation is
// not used in distributed training.
// TODO(mrry): This field is a patch for isolate_session_state and an
// uniform API with flexibility in distributed runtime is needed.
bool share_session_state_in_clusterspec_propagation = 8;
```

If these words satisfy your concerns, I will add them to this PR as a new commit.

@josh11b Get the point!
Please review the updated comment. I have pushed the change as a new commit.
Thanks a lot!

